This is explained in [Create and use ASP.NET Core Razor components](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/blazor/components?view=aspnetcore-3.0), specifically in the  [Component Parameters](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/blazor/components?view=aspnetcore-3.0#component-parameters) section.

`[Parameter]` is used to mark the component parameters that can be set when the component is used in another page. Borrowing from the doc example this component doesn&#39;t have any parameters :

```
&lt;div class=&quot;panel panel-default&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;panel-heading&quot;&gt;@Title&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;panel-body&quot;&gt;@ChildContent&lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;button class=&quot;btn btn-primary&quot; @onclick=&quot;OnClick&quot;&gt;
        Trigger a Parent component method
    &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

@code {
    public string Title { get; set; }

    public RenderFragment ChildContent { get; set; }

    public EventCallback&lt;MouseEventArgs&gt; OnClick { get; set; }
}
```

Without the `[Parameter]` attribute, those are just public properties that can&#39;t be set from other pages. The following line would be invalid :

```
&lt;ChildComponent Title=&quot;Panel Title from Parent&quot; /&gt;
```


While this :

```
&lt;div class=&quot;panel panel-default&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;panel-heading&quot;&gt;@Title&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;panel-body&quot;&gt;@ChildContent&lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;button class=&quot;btn btn-primary&quot; @onclick=&quot;OnClick&quot;&gt;
        Trigger a Parent component method
    &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

@code {
    [Parameter]
    public string Title { get; set; }

    [Parameter]
    public RenderFragment ChildContent { get; set; }

    [Parameter]
    public EventCallback&lt;MouseEventArgs&gt; OnClick { get; set; }
}
```

Allows us to set the parameters whenever we use that component :

```
&lt;ChildComponent Title=&quot;Panel Title from Parent&quot;
                OnClick=&quot;@ShowMessage&quot;&gt;
    Content of the child component is supplied
    by the parent component.
&lt;/ChildComponent&gt;
```

